ume Discount Triggers\n\nQuarterly volume discounts above the rebate ladder apply automatically on the following category-level triggers:\n\n* Category A spend exceeds £1.2m in a quarter: additional 1.0% on Category A\n\n* Category C spend exceeds £1.0m in a quarter: additional 0.75% on Category C\n\n* Category E spend exceeds £900k in a quarter: additional 1.0% on Category E\n\n# 5. Currency and Payment\n\n5.1 UK invoices in GBP. EU invoices in EUR at the local site’s billing entity.\n\n5.2 Foreign exchange risk is borne by the Supplier. No FX-related price adjustments are permitted within the first twelve (12) months.\n\n5.3 Payment terms per MSA clause 6 (90 days from receipt of valid invoice).\n\n# 6. Open-Book Costing for Top-50 SKUs\n\nFor the fifty (50) highest-spend SKUs as identified by Buyer from time to time, Supplier shall provide open-book costing comprising landed cost, Supplier margin, and any rebates received from upstream manufacturers. Buyer reserves the right to require margin compression where Supplier margin exceeds twelve percent (12%) on any open-book SKU.\n\n# 7. Most-Favoured-Customer\n\nSupplier represents that, for substantially comparable Goods supplied on substantially comparable terms, the prices quoted under this Pricing Schedule are no less favourable than those offered to any other customer of Supplier. Supplier shall promptly notify Buyer of any improvement in pricing offered to a third party and shall extend such improvement to Buyer.\n\n# 8. Pricing Schedule Return Format\n\nBidders shall return Appendix A as an Excel workbook with the columns set out in the template. PDF returns will not be accepted. Bidders must also provide:\n\n* A written justification for any SKU where the quoted ceiling price exceeds Buyer’s internal benchmark by more than twenty percent (20%) (Buyer will share benchmark deltas during the clarification window with shortlisted bidders);\n\n* An explanation of methodology for any FX, freight, or duty assumptions baked into landed cost;\n\n* A statement of any sustainability premia included in pricing (e.g. low-carbon steel, recycled-content fasteners).\n\n# Appendix A — SKU Master List (Extract)\n\nSKU | Description | UoM | Indicative annual qty | Bid ceiling price (£)\nA-0001 | HSS twist drill bit, 6mm | each | 12,400 | __________\nA-0002 | Carbide insert, CCMT 09T308 | each | 38,200 | __________\nA-0103 | Diamond abrasive disc, 230mm | each | 6,900 | __________\nB-0044 | M12 hex bolt, A2-70, 60mm | each | 184,000 | __________\nC-0017 | ISO VG 68 hydraulic oil | 208L drum | 412 | __________\nD-0202 | Cut-resistant glove level D, size L | pair | 24,800 | __________\nE-0091 | 3-phase induction motor 5.5kW IE3 | each | 92 | __________\nF-0028 | Pneumatic cylinder ISO 15552 80x200 | each | 148 | __________\nG-0007 | Bearing 6308-2RS | each | 2,420 | __________\n\n_[Full SKU master list of 1,247 lines provided as separate Excel workbook on portal — extract above is illustrative.]_\n\n---\n## Footnotes",
